<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="586" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.52/2065a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-12T16:00:00-05:00">December 12, 1936—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>217. Your 211 December 11, 1 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d586fn23">Not
                                printed.</note> In your forthcoming conference with the President of
                            Mexico the Department authorizes you in your discretion to discuss the
                            Yaqui Valley situation, being guided by your knowledge of the status of
                            the proposals submitted by the landowners.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>